Package alfdozen.es_2023_2sem_terca_teira_leipl_grupoa

Class Schedule

java.lang.Object
alfdozen.es_2023_2sem_terca_teira_leipl_grupoa.Schedule
final class Schedule extends Object
The Schedule class is used to represent a schedule of lectures for a student. It contains a list of Lectures and information about the student, such as their name and student number. The constructor can be used to create an empty schedule or a schedule with a list of lectures, as well as providing student information. The student number must be a positive integer and will be validated by the class. The class can also add or remove lectures to/from the schedule. The class can be sorted by the time slots of the lectures in the schedule. The toString() method returns a String representation of the schedule, including the student name and number, as well as the list of lectures. If the student name or number is not provided, the string "Unknown" will be used instead. If the schedule is empty, the string "Schedule is empty" will be returned.
Version:
1.0.0
Author:
alfdozen

    • loadWebcal

      static Schedule loadWebcal(String uri) throws IOException
      This method loads a schedule via a webcal URI. The webcal should lead to an iCalendar file. If there are no compatible events inside the iCalendar file, the method returns a Schedule without lectures.
      Parameters:
      uri - the webcal URI that leads to an iCalendar file.
      Returns:
      a schedule object with all lectures in the iCalendar.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - is thrown if the URI is null or not a webcall URI.
      MalformedURLException - is thrown if the URI cannot be converted into an HTTPS URL.
      IOException - is thrown if an error is given when connecting or reading file with HTTPS protocol.
      See Also:
      • Webcal Wikipedia Entry

    • readICalendar

      static Schedule readICalendar(BufferedReader reader) throws IOException
      This method reads an ICalendar file from the BufferedReader and parses it into a schedule. If user information is found, it is added to the schedule. Each event (if compatible) of the iCalendar is parsed into a lecture and added into the schedule. The schedule is then returned.
      Parameters:
      reader - the buffered reader used to read the iCalendar file.
      Returns:
      a schedule object with all lectures in the iCalendar.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - is thrown if the file does not have the standard iCalendar structure.
      IOException - is thrown if an error is given when reading file with HTTPS protocol.

    • skipReadUntilStartsWith

      static String skipReadUntilStartsWith(BufferedReader reader, Pattern startPattern) throws IOException
      This method reads lines from the BufferedReader until it finds a line that starts with the provided pattern. If found, the prefix matching the pattern is removed from the line string and it is returned. Otherwise, returns null.
      Parameters:
      reader - the buffered reader used to find the line with the prefix pattern.
      startPattern - the pattern that the prefix of the line must match.
      Returns:
      a string of the line where the pattern matched the prefix, but without said prefix.
      Throws:
      IOException - is thrown if an error is given when reading file with HTTPS protocol.

    • transformEventToLecture

      static Lecture transformEventToLecture(BufferedReader reader) throws IOException
      This method reads the event information with the BufferedReader, transforms it into a lecture and returns the lecture. If the event does not mention a course, or if no event is found, the method returns null. The Fenix iCalendars do not mention room capacity, students enrolled, degree or class group. These attributes will be null regardless of how complete the iCalendar is.
      Parameters:
      reader - the buffered reader used to parse the event.
      Returns:
      a lecture object with the event information.
      Throws:
      IOException - is thrown if an error is given when reading file with HTTPS protocol.

    • buildDateTimeInformation

      static LocalDateTime[] buildDateTimeInformation(String dateTimeBegin, String dateTimeEnd)
      Transforms the event's datetime start and datetime end strings into LocalDateTime objects. Returns an array with both objects. If the a LocalDateTime object cannot be parsed from a string, that object is returned as null.
      Parameters:
      dateTimeBegin - the beginning date and time of the event as String.
      dateTimeEnd - the ending date and time of the event as String.
      Returns:
      a localdatetime array with the beginning and ending datetimes of the event.

    • getMapCoursesCounts

      private static void getMapCoursesCounts(Map<String,Integer> mapLectures, String course, Lecture lecture)
      This auxiliary method receives a lecture and checks if it has the received course and the same weekday and hour as other lectures in the map. If so, it adds one to that entry. Otherwise, it creates a new entry with the value 1. Then, it returns the map of unique weekday lectures.
      Parameters:
      mapLectures - the map with the lecture string as the key and count as the value.
      course - the course for the lecture being matched.
      lecture - the lectures to check and count.
